# Frontend Conventions — Next.js + Tailwind CSS

## Component Rules
- **Functional components only** — no class components
- Every component must have a TypeScript `Props` interface defined above the component
- Default export for page-level components; named exports for shared components
- Components must be pure — no direct API calls inside JSX; use custom hooks

```typescript
// ✅ Correct component structure
interface ArticleCardProps {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  status: ArticleStatus;
  tags: string[];
  viewCount: number;
  likeCount: number;
  commentCount: number;
}

export const ArticleCard: React.FC<ArticleCardProps> = ({
  id, title, status, tags, viewCount, likeCount, commentCount
}) => {
  return (
    <div className="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-4 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
      {/* ... */}
    </div>
  );
};
```

## Custom Hooks (data fetching layer)
- All API calls must live in a custom hook (`src/hooks/use[Resource].ts`)
- Never call `fetch` or `axios` directly inside a component
- Hooks return `{ data, isLoading, error, refetch }` shape

```typescript
// src/hooks/useArticles.ts
export const useArticles = (filters?: ArticleFilters) => {
  const [articles, setArticles] = useState<Article[]>([]);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const fetchArticles = async () => {
    try {
      setIsLoading(true);
      const data = await articleApi.list(filters);
      setArticles(data);
    } catch (err) {
      setError('Failed to load articles');
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  };

  useEffect(() => { fetchArticles(); }, []);
  return { articles, isLoading, error, refetch: fetchArticles };
};
```

## API Client Layer
All backend calls must go through typed API client functions in `src/lib/api/`:

```typescript
// src/lib/api/articles.api.ts
import { ApiResponse, Article } from '@/types';

const BASE_URL = '/api/v1';

export const articleApi = {
  list: async (filters?: ArticleFilters): Promise<Article[]> => {
    const params = new URLSearchParams(filters as Record<string, string>);
    const res = await fetch(`${BASE_URL}/articles?${params}`);
    const json: ApiResponse<Article[]> = await res.json();
    if (!json.success) throw new Error(json.error);
    return json.data!;
  },
  // ...
};
```

## Tailwind CSS Rules
- **Tailwind only** — no custom CSS files, no inline `style={{}}` attributes
- Use Tailwind's design system tokens; do not use arbitrary values unless absolutely needed
- Responsive design: always consider mobile-first (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)
- Dark mode: not required for MVP, but use semantic color classes

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<button className="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded-lg transition-colors">
  Submit for Review
</button>

// ❌ Wrong
<button style={{ backgroundColor: '#2563EB', color: 'white' }}>
  Submit for Review
</button>
```
