## Shared Cross-Role Components
These live outside any single feature role and are maintained collectively. Whoever touches them must notify all roles that consume them via the PR description:
- `src/components/ui/ConfirmationModal.tsx` — used for all destructive actions across the app
- `src/app/(dashboard)/layout.tsx` — global shell: nav, sidebar, notification bell slot
- `src/components/articles/ArticleStatusBadge.tsx` — owned by `content-authoring-engineer`, but also rendered inside `content-moderation-engineer`'s reviewer views — coordinate changes

## Confirmation Modals (required for these actions)
Always use `<ConfirmationModal>` before executing:
- Article submission / re-submission
- Article deletion
- Quiz submission
- Tech Talk publish / delete
- Admin role change / deactivate user
- Reviewer approve / reject

```typescript
// src/components/ui/ConfirmationModal.tsx
interface ConfirmationModalProps {
  isOpen: boolean;
  title: string;
  message: string;
  confirmLabel?: string;
  onConfirm: () => void;
  onCancel: () => void;
  isLoading?: boolean;
}
```

## TipTap Rich Text Editor
- Use the shared `<ArticleEditor>` component — never instantiate TipTap directly in pages
- Store content as JSON (not HTML) — convert to HTML only for rendering
- Support: bold, italic, headings, bullet lists, code blocks, image upload

## Status Badges
Use a shared `<ArticleBadge>` component with consistent color mapping:
```typescript
const statusColors: Record<ArticleStatus, string> = {
  Draft: 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-700',
  Pending: 'bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700',
  Published: 'bg-green-100 text-green-700',
  Rejected: 'bg-red-100 text-red-700',
};
```
